The paper deals with algorithmic fairness in machine learning, specifically in the context of regression models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary category of the paper. The paper also involves the use of regularisation techniques, which are commonly used in optimization problems in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the estimation of information-theoretic divergences, which is a topic in coding theory and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also deals with fairness criteria, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the use of statistical techniques to measure group fairness criteria, which is a topic in computational statistics (cs.CE).
